":"https:\/\/github.com\/arodic","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcwODk4NA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"arodic","type":"User","id":708984,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Just confirmed, `extractRotation()` is the problem. The returned rotation matrix is not clean when any scale axis is negative.","created_at":"2018-05-28T21:20:29.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14158#issuecomment-392605095","id":392605095,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14158","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5MjYwNTA5NQ==","updated_at":"2018-05-28T21:20:29.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/392605095","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/708984?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/arodic","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcwODk4NA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"arodic","type":"User","id":708984,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"As soon as you allow negative scale, the implied quaternion is no longer unique.\r\n\r\nConsider `matrix.makeScale( - 1, 1, - 1 )`. \r\n\r\nThat can be interpreted as a reflection through X and Z with rotation zero; it can also be interpreted as a pure rotation around Y of 180 degrees.\r\n","created_at":"2018-05-28T21:31:26.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14158#issuecomment-392606253","id":392606253,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14158","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5MjYwNjI1Mw==","updated_at":"2018-05-28T21:31:26.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/392606253","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"That makes sense, yet I notice that `decompose()`, which returns expected quaternion, internally  does something similar. It creates what looks like rotation matrix, then creates a quaternion from that matrix with `quaternion.setFromRotationMatrix( matrix );`. But it appears it is not a pure rotation matrix, and it inverts elements 0, 1 and 2 when determinant is negative. That is why I assumed that determinant inversion was causing the discrepancy between `decompose()` and quarternion from extracted rotation matrix.","created_at":"2018-05-28T21:49:57.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14158#issuecomment-392608199","id":392608199,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14158","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5MjYwODE5OQ==","updated_at":"2018-05-28T21:49:57.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/392608199","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/708984?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/arodic","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcwODk4NA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"arodic","type":"User","id":708984,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/orgs"}},{"index":8,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Actually, `extractRotation()` is not even correct because it fails to set all the matrix elements.\r\n\r\n@arodic Maybe you can use `decompose()`, instead, extracting the quaternion.\r\n\r\n\/ping @Mugen87 Can you avoid using the method in `Reflector`, `Refractor`, and `Water`?\r\n","created_at":"2018-05-28T23:33:22.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14158#issuecomment-392617026","id":392617026,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14158","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5MjYxNzAyNg==","updated_at":"2018-05-28T23:36:53.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/392617026","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":9,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@WestLangley I ended up using decompose instead but I find it less semantically intuitive because it mutates the arguments and I didn't really need translate and scale so I had to pass two dummy vectors to make it work.","created_at":"2018-05-29T07:05:01.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14158#issuecomment-392673836","id":392673836,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14158","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5MjY3MzgzNg==","updated_at":"2018-05-29T07:05:01.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/392673836","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/708984?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/arodic","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcwODk4NA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"arodic","type":"User","id":708984,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/orgs"}},{"index":10,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"> Can you avoid using the method in Reflector, Refractor, and Water?\r\n\r\nBasically yes. Instead of:\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/4fab7a7d3e2ccc32a1f43a24a8dce39a873bbcf5\/examples\/js\/objects\/Reflector.js#L81-L85\r\nwe could do this:\r\n```js\r\nscope.matrixWorld.decompose( position, quaternion, scale );\r\n\r\nnormal.set( 0, 0, 1 );\r\nnormal.applyQuaternion( quaternion );\r\n\r\n```","created_at":"2018-05-29T09:00:16.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14158#issuecomment-392704626","id":392704626,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14158","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5MjcwNDYyNg==","updated_at":"2018-05-29T09:00:32.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/392704626","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":11,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"For historical perspective, the three.js paradigm has always been to control an object's transform by specifying `position`, `quaternion`, and `scale`. Scale was assumed to be positive.\r\n\r\nThis paradigm only supports pure rotations, and it is more limiting than specifying a matrix transform, which additionally supports reflections and shearing.\r\n\r\nDue to demand, we more recently added support for negative scale factors. We can clearly see the problems that arise when a feature does not work universally. (FWIW, another example would be `Mesh.drawMode`.)\r\n\r\nWe can try to 'fix' `extractRotation()`, but I am not sure that is possible based on my earlier comments.\r\n\r\nWe can also remove it.\r\n\r\n@arodic and @Mugen87 will you consider using alternate methods in the code you are maintaining, so this method is no longer used in the library?","created_at":"2018-05-29T11:52:56.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/gith